benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/block - Block an account

covered: Valid Payload: Successful blocking scenarios are well covered with valid payloads.
Invalid Payload: Multiple scenarios test for malformed or missing fields, ensuring proper error responses.
Server Error Handling: Scenarios simulate database unavailability and unauthorized access, covering server error responses.
gaps: Duplicate Submission: No tests specifically address how the system handles duplicate submissions of the same blocking state.
Large Payloads: No tests cover the handling of very large payloads for the BlockingState.
Concurrency Issues: No scenarios test for race conditions when multiple requests attempt to block the same account simultaneously.
recommendations: Add tests for duplicate submissions to ensure the system handles them gracefully.
Include scenarios for large payloads to test the limits of the BlockingState.
Add tests for concurrency issues to verify system behavior under simultaneous requests.
